  <h1 class="project-title">Optimizing your user interviews</h1>
  <hr>
  <div class="text-wrap">
    <p>
    I used to be intimidated by the idea of participating in, leading, and
    coordinating user interviews. I was sure that there was a very correct
    process for the whole thing that I'd mess up. Now that I've had more
    experience with interviews and the research process, I wanted to share some
    of the things I've learned from trial and error.
    </p>
    <p>
      It's not nearly as scary or unforgiving as I had imagined. You can be
      precise without trying to be too careful. And the more you do it the easier
      it gets. Hopefully a few of these tips help you get started leading your
      own interviews.
    </p>
  </div>
