  <p>
    Using a service like Calendly makes it easier on the interviewee to find a
    time most convenient for them and you don’t get caught trying to juggle
    a myriad of potential times you suggested to different people.
  </p>

  <h6>When not to schedule an interview</h6>
  <p>
    After learning this the hard way, I now <em>always</em> leave 30min breaks
    between bookings (another feature of Calendly). This time is valuable for
    catching up on last minute notes you need to jot down or debrief with someone
    on what you learned from the interview.
  </p>
  <p>
    And if you're like me, you'll be ready for a few minutes to chill.
    Introversion is real.
  </p>
</div>

