<div class="text-wrap">
  <p>
    Take my word for it, don't schedule interviews on Fridays. You probably
    won’t be in the mood after a long week of interviews and neither will your
    interviewee. Work days can be very lax/fluid on Fridays. Having a time
    constraint is just kind of a bummer.
  </p>

  <h6>How to be prepared</h6>
  <p>
    Know how many people you need to interview and be sure to schedule a few
    more interviews than you need. People are busy and schedules can be chaotic;
    some people will inevitably have to cancel last minute.
  </p>
  <p>
    Send reminder emails the morning of the interview. While an extra email
    might be annoying, it decreases the risk that they’ll forget about the
    interview or confuse the start time. People have busy lives it happens!
  </p>
  <p>
    Record who you’ve reached out to (Intercom has a nice "last contacted"
    filter). I'm a fan of Trello. I keep a trello board of the interview roster
    which helps me easily keep track of what's up next and what has been
    completed.
  </p>
</div>
