  <h6>Leave the awkward silence</h6>
  <p>
    Your job as the interviewer is to do more listening than talking. If you
    try to fill in the silence you might influence the interviewee's answer and
    disrupt their thinking. And for the interviewee, the silence really isn’t
    that awkward.
  </p>
  <p>
    Be sure not suggest answers to fill in the space or out of nervousness.
    Expand on a question or give examples if you are asked to. You might sway
    their answer.
  </p>

  <h6>Karma</h6>
  <p>
    Always take the last minute or two to ask how you can return the favor.
    Follow through on anything your promise to do in return! And of course,
    only promise things you know that you can follow through on.
  </p>
